7. Basic Terms which will be used further: 
- Object -> instance of a class. 
    -> have properties and behaviours. 
    -> has a physical existence. 
    -> eg. dog is a class => tommy is an object. 

- Class -> blueprint that describes the properties and behaviours of objects. 
    -> have data members and member functions. 
    -> no physical existence. 

- Methods -> behaviours 
    -> get inputs. do certain tasks and return some value.
    -> can be invoked 

- Instance Variables -> non-static data members. stored in heap memory within object area. 
    -> Lifetime - till object is there in heap memory.
- Class Variables -> Static data members. 
    -> Lifetime - till class definition is loaded in memory.
- Local Variables -> eg. defined in a method.
    -> Lifetime - till method ends. 
- Access Modifiers -> default, public , protected, private 
    -> Default - no accesss modifier is written. 
- Non Access Modifiers ->  final, abstract, strictfp
- Arrays -> multiple values of same type under a single name. 
- Enums -> var is restricted to some pre-defined values. 
- Interfaces -> contains declaration but not implementation. 

