- final int a = 4; // cant rewrite it then
- Use '+' to combine strings, ints, chars etc. // concatenation
- int a = 4, b = 5, c = 6; 
- int a , b , c;
  a = b = c = 50; 

9. Identifiers: 
- unique names 
- contains letters, nums, $, _ 
- starts with letters, $, _ 
- case sensitive 
- no whitespaces 
- no reserved words 

